        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold accent-orange mb-6 text-center">The Turn: The Corrective Flow</h3>

        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">This four-step sequence ensures space is created before the correct motor pattern is loaded, preventing Anterior Femoral Glide.</p>



        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">

                        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-accent-teal/10 border-b-4 border-accent-teal shadow-md flex flex-col text-center">

                <span class="text-5xl accent-teal mb-3">&#8618;</span>

                <p class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-800">STEP 1: De-Compress</p>

                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2 font-mono">LATERAL DISTRACTION</p>

                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Pulls the thigh *outward* to create max joint space and de-pinch the capsule. (This step replaces the need for immediate SMFR.)</p>

            </div>

                        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-accent-orange/10 border-b-4 border-accent-orange shadow-md flex flex-col text-center">

                <span class="text-5xl accent-orange mb-3">&#10515;</span>

                <p class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-800">STEP 2: Anchor</p>

                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2 font-mono">90/90 HIP LIFT (PPT)</p>

                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Establishes the Posterior Pelvic Tilt to "raise the roof" of the hip socket. </p>

            </div>

                        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-accent-teal/10 border-b-4 border-accent-teal shadow-md flex flex-col text-center">

                <span class="text-5xl accent-teal mb-3">&#8617;</span>

                <p class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-800">STEP 3: Posterior Glide</p>

                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2 font-mono">WALL ABDUCTION (Heel Drive)</p>

                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Neurologically forces the specific posterior glute fibers to pull the femur head *back*.</p>

            </div>

                        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-accent-orange/10 border-b-4 border-accent-orange shadow-md flex flex-col text-center">

                <span class="text-5xl accent-orange mb-3">&#128170;</span>

                <p class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-800">STEP 4: Load Pattern</p>

                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2 font-mono">RDL / GOBLET SQUAT</p>

                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Integrates the new PPT/Glute pattern under resistance for long-term stability.</p>

            </div>

        </div>

    </section>



        <section class="mb-12">

        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold accent-dark mb-6 text-center">The 4-Week Accelerated Chart</h3>

        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">Frequency is high in the stabilization phases (Wk 1/2) and shifts to dedicated loading sessions (3x/Week) in the integration phases (Wk 3/4).</p>



        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">

                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-playful border-l-8 border-accent-teal">

                <h4 class="text-3xl font-extrabold accent-teal mb-2">WEEK 1: De-Load & Anchor</h4>

                <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-4">Goal: Stop Pain / Master PPT</p>

                <div class="space-y-4">

                    <p class="text-sm font-bold bg-accent-gold/50 p-2 rounded-md">Restriction: STRICTLY avoid Frog Pose, Deep Squats.</p>

                    <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-3 text-gray-700">

                        <li><span class="font-bold"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=igUoMHwIL8A" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Lateral Banded Distraction</a>:</span> Band pulls thigh outward. (3x / day, 2 min holds.)</li>

                        <li><span class="font-bold"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4NqvBm6-Neg" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">90/90 Hip Lift</a>:</span> Master Posterior Pelvic Tilt. (3 sets of 10 breaths.)</li>

                    </ul>

                    <p class="text-sm font-bold accent-dark">Frequency: Daily (Pain-Free Only)</p>

                </div>

            </div>



                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-playful border-l-8 border-accent-teal">

                <h4 class="text-3xl font-extrabold accent-teal mb-2">WEEK 2: Re-Align & Activate</h4>

                <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-4">Goal: Posterior Glide Recruitment</p>

                <div class="space-y-4">

                    <p class="text-sm font-bold bg-gray-100 p-2 rounded-md accent-dark">Mechanism: Glute Max + Posterior Glute Medius Dominance. Inhibit TFL.</p>

                    <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-3 text-gray-700">

                        <li><span class="font-bold"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aPbiOoNz2Ws" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Isometric Wall Abduction (Heel Drive)</a>:</span> Push heel into wall. (3 sets of 30s holds.) **(Crucial)**</li>

                        <li><span class="font-bold"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6eL6Ax1zMik" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Cook Hip Lift</a>:</span> Single-leg bridge holding opposite knee to chest. (Forces Glute Max activation.)</li>

                        <li><span class="font-bold">Side-Lying Leg Lift:</span> Toe angled down to bias posterior fibers. (Max 3-inch lift.)</li>

                        <li><span class="font-bold">Quadruped Adductor Rockback:</span> Gentle rock only to inner-thigh stretch, stopping before pinch.</li>

                        <li><span class="font-bold">Dead Bugs:</span> Low-level core work, forcing Anti-Extension.</li>

                    </ul>

                    <p class="text-sm font-bold accent-dark">Frequency: 4x / Week</p>

                </div>

            </div>



                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-playful border-l-8 border-accent-orange">

                <h4 class="text-3xl font-extrabold accent-orange mb-2">WEEK 3: Functional Patterning</h4>

                <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-4">Goal: The Glute-Dominated Hinge (Low Load)</p>

                <div class="space-y-4">

                    <p class="text-sm font-bold bg-gray-100 p-2 rounded-md accent-dark">Mechanism: Transition stabilization into fundamental compound movements without impingement.</p>

                    <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-3 text-gray-700">

                        <li><span class="font-bold"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WGjf5w8iaTM" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Box Squats</a>:</span> Squat down to a high box. Focus on sitting back. Stop above pinch depth.</li>

                        <li><span class="font-bold">RDL (Romanian Deadlift):</span> Light dumbbells. Focus on hips-back movement. Keep shins vertical.</li>

                        <li><span class="font-bold">Copenhagen Plank (Regression):</span> Side plank with top knee on bench. Eccentric adductor control.</li>

                        <li><span class="font-bold accent-teal">Daily Vitamin:</span> Perform Wall Abduction isometric hold before every session.</li>

                    </ul>

                    <p class="text-sm font-bold accent-dark">Frequency: 3x / Week</p>

            </div>

            </div>



                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-playful border-l-8 border-accent-orange">

                <h4 class="text-3xl font-extrabold accent-orange mb-2">WEEK 4: Full Functional Load</h4>

                <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-4">Goal: Solidify the new motor pattern under resistance.</p>

                <div class="space-y-4">

                    <p class="text-sm font-bold bg-gray-100 p-2 rounded-md accent-dark">Mechanism: Load Tolerance & Volume. Increase load/volume while maintaining perfect PPT control.</p>

                    <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-3 text-gray-700">

                        <li><span class="font-bold"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mF5tnEBrdkc" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Goblet Squats (Full Depth Test)</a>:</span> Weight counterbalances torso. Test depth, stop if pinch occurs.</li>

                        <li><span class="font-bold">Split Squats:</span> Focus on vertical front shin. Controlled descent.</li>

                        <li><span class="font-bold">Standing Single-Leg RDLS:</span> Advanced unilateral control.</li>

                        <li><span class="font-bold">Lifestyle Check:</span> Ensure sitting posture is high-hip and you are avoiding standing hip-hang.</li>

                    </ul>

                    <p class="text-sm font-bold accent-dark">Frequency: 3x / Week</p>

            </div>

            </div>

        </div>

